webnn: give the Windows ORT backend its own fp16 dep.

graph_builder_ort.cc / tensor_impl_ort.cc include the fp16 shim, whose
include dir upstream arrives only transitively through the TFLite deps.
With webnn_use_tflite=false (the miniblink2 SDK trim) the path vanishes
and the Windows-only ort/ sources fail to find <fp16/fp16.h>. Direct dep
states the real dependency; no change when TFLite is on.

--- a/services/webnn/BUILD.gn	2026-07-08 22:59:18
+++ b/services/webnn/BUILD.gn	2026-07-08 22:59:18
@@ -285,6 +285,10 @@
 
   if (is_win) {
     deps += [
+      # The ort/ backend uses the fp16 conversion helpers directly; upstream
+      # only gets the include dir transitively via the TFLite deps, which the
+      # miniblink2 SDK build compiles out (webnn_use_tflite=false).
+      "//third_party/fp16",
       "//services/webnn/host",
       "//ui/gfx/mojom",
     ]
